description: This stately Presidio Heights property features 4 bedrooms on one level all with en-suite bathrooms making it an ideal family home. Bathroom offers double vanity sinks, skylight and walk in closet. Two large bedrooms have view to the backyard. Newly fenced private backyard perfect for entertaining. Many more upgrades that you won't want to miss this home!

description: A true piece of SF history, this 4bd/4ba Mediterranean-style SFH was once the studio of renowned architect Edward Young. Elegant triple-arched windows are a signature element of his, echoed in arched passageways throughout. The home continues to inspire, thoughtfully renovated for todaPy's living. The main floor plan flows seamlessly outdoors, ideal for hosting. A sunny central courtyard is the highlight, protected from breezes and a great place for brunch. Spacious public rooms have a gracious feel, enhanced by ornate mantel carvings, curved columns, elegant stained glass, and an original chandelier. The updated kitchen and fam. rm. flow together with the back patio, letting you choose between indoor and outdoor fireplaces. Three bdrms are on the upper level, including the primary suite w/full bath, walk-in closet, and walkout deck. A skylight brightens the hall bath. The lower level guest rm. can serve as an au-pair space, w adj. laundry and full bath, and dir. access to yard/garage

From the trademark glass floor and towering skylights to the full wall of windows boasting unrivaled downtown and Bay views, you’ll wonder if the sensation of walking on air arises from the polished, airy Organic Modern design or from knowing that you have the inside scoop on this off-market listing in one of SF’s sunniest and most prized neighborhoods. The spacious private backyard, peerless owner’s retreat, true chef’s kitchen with waterfall counters, glass wine cellar, nearly 13x22 rec-room, and wide entertainers’ balconies are all part of this spectacular parcel, all outfitted in no-expense-spared fittings and shimmering with the irreplaceable spark of artistic inspiration.

description: Perched above Eureka Valley and the Castro, and a short walk from Noe Valley and 24th Street's restaurants and stores, this 4 unit building offers an incredible owner's unit with the benefit of supplemental income coming from the other 3 units. description: Behind the simple facade of 305 Filbert, with its distinctive, sepia-hued mural, is a wonderful 2+ bedroom, 2.5-bath home, with views of the Bay & beyond.  Fewer than 10 years ago, the property was thoughtfully updated to create indoor & outdoor spaces for entertaining or relaxing.  From the front you see views of the Bay & the Filbert Steps garden, while as you go up to the middle & then third floors, the views grow grander, eventually being framed by floor-to-ceiling sliding glass doors in the master suite.  The middle level opens onto an area perfect for an office, separated with glass doors from a den that can be used as a sleeping room.  Down the hall is a rear bedroom.  All the windows on this level have Bay and/or garden views.  The ground floor has a combined living-dining area & an open kitchen, which overlook a rear, enclosed patio with decorative brick pavers. Located on the Filbert Steps, the house has no garage, but is minutes by foot to North Beach shops & restaurants.

Steps from the Financial District's premier fashion and gastronomy hub lined with boutiques and fine dining hotspots including Quince, Bixx, Kokkari and Cotogna, this rare architectural gem offers refined, cosmopolitan living at its finest.

description:
Live the Mission Dolores dream in this three-bedroom, split bath, 1584 sqft  Mission Dolores flat adjoining Dolores Park with separate dining room, living room, verdant backyard, garage parking, and luxury finishes. 

Live — 555 Dolores Street is adjacent to San Francisco's beloved Dolores Park, 16 acres of green space, tennis and basketball courts, flower gardens, children's playground, downtown city views, and lively weekend fun. Stroll to The Gastro microhood on 18th Street for Bi-Rite Market, Bi-Rite Creamery, Delfina, Pizzeria Delfina, Tartine Bakery, and Namu Gaji. Nearby Valencia Street corridor is home to beloved restaurants including Lazy Bear and Commonwealth, cafes including Four Barrel and Ritual, bars including Zeitgeist and Beretta and boutiques including 826 Valencia's Pirate Supply and Paxton's Gate for peg legs, raccoon bones, et al.

Commute — MUNI J-Church line stops at Dolores Park for a quick commute to SOMA. BART at 16th and Mission is a stroll away for East and South Bay commuters.

Listen — Six music amps wired to two JBL 2-way, 8-inch in-ceiling speakers in each of six rooms: three bedrooms, living room, dining room, and the kitchen. Play anything in any room from the Sonos app.

Light — Architectural pendants and semi-flush light fixtures from Bover, Zaneen, and TechLighting using energy-efficient, full-spectrum LED lighting controlled by wireless Lutron dimmer switches. Control all lighting in any room from an app.

Cook — Contemporary SieMatic handleless kitchen cabinetry and floating shelves, Calacatta marble slab honed counter and backsplash, Fisher-Paykel stainless steel refrigerator, Bertazzoni stainless steel range and oven, Miele hood, and dishwasher. Bi-Rite Market is around the corner on 18th Street for inspiration and ingredients.

Entertain — Flora Grubb designed backyard paradise with raised deck, BBQ, deck couch and chairs, dining table, and native plant landscaping.


Bonus — Lovely period finishes including cove ceilings, crown molding, and wainscoting. Nest thermostat and smoke/CO2 detectors. Hansgrohe bathroom fixtures. Polished wood floors. New in-unit Miele washer and dryer. Security gate. Friendly, professional, and quiet neighbors.

description:
The historic Seventy2 Townsend is located in the highly sought-after South Beach neighborhood along the Embarcadero. It is a boutique building with a luxurious aesthetic. 
Residence #702 is a 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom condo with breathtaking views of the water and the Bay Bridge. Upgrades in the home include Studio Becker cabinetry, Caesarstone counters, wide-plank hardwood flooring, and a Bosch and Thermador appliance package. The home features beautifully appointed interiors and its own balcony.

Historic and contemporary: find the best of both worlds at Seventy2 Townsend. Formerly home to the historic Hooper's South End Grain Warehouse, 72 Townsend has been meticulously restored and converted into South Beach's premier boutique offering with 74 residences along the Embarcadero. Built by KB Homes, these modern residences come with custom-designed finishes; gas kitchens with Bosch and Thermador appliances; and balconies. Amenities for the nine-story condominium building include a front desk attendant, outdoor sky terrace, and dedicated 1:1 parking. These bespoke homes blend historic authenticity with modern luxury in the heart of San Francisco's South Beach. Seventy2 Townsend is conveniently located near Oracle Park, multiple restaurants, and the Ferry Building, and is close to a variety of transportation choices.

UNIT FEATURES:

* 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom
* Gorgeous water and Bay Bridge views
* home office nook
* 1,212 sq. ft. per developer
* Balcony
* Kitchen features Studio Becker cabinetry, Caesarstone counters, Bosch and Thermador appliances
* Wide-plank hardwood floors
* Designer upgrades
* Washer/dryer in unit
* Assigned 1-car parking
* Current HOA dues: $912.23 per month

BUILDING FEATURES:

* Boutique building with outdoor sky terrace and second-floor hospitality lounge
* Lobby attendant 40 hours a week
* 2 elevators
* Unit separation walls upgraded with 2-hour construction, STC Rating of 57
* Insulated heat pump and washer/dryer rooms
* Acousti-Mat underlayment under hard surface flooring
* Close to multiple transportation options
* Near Oracle Park, Ferry Building, the Embarcadero, and much more.

description: Perfectly positioned in Pacific Heights, 2401 Green St is a gracious single family home that thoughtfully blends original details with contemporary finishes and boasts 4 beds and 3.5 baths across three levels. description: Perfectly situated in Cole Valley, sits a wonderfully charming condominium that is a leisurely distance to shopping, parks and muni. As you make your way through the front door, you are greeted by a generously proportioned entrance, making for the perfect place to shed coats and keys. As you round the corner to the living room, the open flow perfectly marries the front three rooms of the home together. The luxury appointed kitchen pulls at the heartstrings of your inner foodie. Down the hall past the thoughtfully designed bathroom, are two lovely bedrooms that are perfectly distanced from the entertaining space. The custom closets round out the primary bedroom with unparalleled storage. As you make your way outside to the deck, on the far side of the yard, you can catch a glimpse of olives growing on the tree in the back. The versatility of the layout, mixed with the generous outdoor space and location, truly creates an ideal urban sanctuary!

description: Historic Cottage Row condo in a charming garden setting: 3 steps from the landscaped brick path to your front door. The high ceilings and period detail will charm you. The updated bath and renovated kitchen will impress! In-unit laundry. Additional deeded storage. This 2 bedroom home has it all. Located in the Lower Pacific Heights neighborhood, Cottage Row is a picturesque walkway that connects Sutter to Bush streets between Webster and Fillmore. It combines the tranquility of a mini-park with easy access to dining, shopping, and nightlife at Japantown Center and Fillmore Street. The condo is a unit in one of 22 Victorian houses built by William Hollis in the late 1800s. They form the Bush Street-Cottage Row Historic District, which is listed in the National Register of Historic Places. This unique slice of San Francisco has a rich history and is a peaceful oasis in a vibrant neighborhood.

description: This beautifully renovated 4BD/3BA semi-detached home offers gorgeous interiors & a large private yard, w/ spectacular Central-Richmond amenities and outdoor space right outside your door. description: This fairytale cottage located in Sunnyside (boarding Glen Park) offers a unique chance to both enjoy & escape urban living. Take a cobblestone path through tiered gardens to reach the front door, tucked back from the street for a tranquil feel. Open entertaining areas flow beautifully outdoors, gushing with light as they overlook the freshly landscaped front yard. Beyond the kitchen window, a patio offers an intimate space for morning coffee. A large laundry room with side-by-side washer doubles as storage, & you'll find more space for off-season clothes or holiday decorations in the detached 1-car garage. Bedrooms are nestled in the back of the home, facing the rear garden. A peaceful way to wake in the city. From the 2nd bedroom, direct backyard access & verdant views of SF hills highlight its versatility as a bedroom or office. The flexible floor plan extends past what meets the eye. RH-2 Zoning provides expansion potential for two condos or two ADUs.

description: This charming and surprisingly spacious home is so much more than what you expect when you see the home from the outside. Do not be fooled. There are two additional bedrooms both generous in size. A kitchen and bathroom at the rear of the home provide direct access to the garden. The garden features mature trees, border landscaping and a nice grassy area for easy enjoyment. The home is detached on the east side which provides additional light to the center of the home. Located a few blocks south of Cortland Ave., Holly Park, and St. Mary's Park,  this home is ready for the next owners to add their own touches.

The Master bedroom has a generous walk-in closet & master bath has a tub with a separate sky-lit walk-in shower. Visit today!

description: Queen Anne style Victorian home restored with meticulous care and attention to detail to its original vintage beauty, updated for contemporary  function and comfort. Extraordinary architectural features include beautiful wood floors, mahogany stained millwork, high ceilings, and elegant period details. The main floor has a bright living room and double parlor/library with marble fireplace, and a gracious dining room. The eat-in kitchen is next to a glorious sun room that extends across the back of the home with a deck and stairs to the landscaped garden. One bedroom and full bath on this floor. Upstairs, two large bedrooms and a full bathroom. The lower level has a workshop that could be developed into a family room or suite with its own entrance, plus laundry and cedar lined storage room. One car parking and storage, plus a storage shed under deck in yard.
